Create a new file at `lib/ui/widgets/routing/jack_painter.dart` that implements a CustomPainter for rendering the jack socket. The painter should draw a visual representation of a 1/8" Eurorack jack with proper styling.

Implementation steps:
1. Create JackPainter class extending CustomPainter
2. Implement paint method to draw jack components:
   - Outer ring (stroke)
   - Inner circle (fill)
   - Center hole (cutout)
   - Color bar based on port type
3. Implement shouldRepaint for optimization
4. Support Material 3 theming

Example code:
```dart
class JackPainter extends CustomPainter {
  final Port port;
  final bool isHovered;
  final bool isSelected;
  final ThemeData theme;

  JackPainter({
    required this.port,
    required this.isHovered,
    required this.isSelected,
    required this.theme,
  });

  @override
  void paint(Canvas canvas, Size size) {
    final center = Offset(size.width / 2, size.height / 2);
    final outerRadius = size.width * 0.4;
    final innerRadius = outerRadius * 0.8;
    final holeRadius = innerRadius * 0.3;

    // Draw outer ring
    final outerPaint = Paint()
      ..color = theme.colorScheme.onSurface
      ..style = PaintingStyle.stroke
      ..strokeWidth = 2.0;
    canvas.drawCircle(center, outerRadius, outerPaint);

    // Draw inner circle
    final innerPaint = Paint()
      ..color = isHovered ? theme.colorScheme.primaryContainer : theme.colorScheme.surface
      ..style = PaintingStyle.fill;
    canvas.drawCircle(center, innerRadius, innerPaint);

    // Draw center hole
    final holePaint = Paint()
      ..color = theme.colorScheme.background
      ..style = PaintingStyle.fill;
    canvas.drawCircle(center, holeRadius, holePaint);

    // Draw color bar based on port type
    final colorBarPaint = Paint()
      ..color = _getPortTypeColor(port.type)
      ..style = PaintingStyle.fill;
    canvas.drawRect(
      Rect.fromLTWH(size.width * 0.1, size.height * 0.8, size.width * 0.8, size.height * 0.1),
      colorBarPaint,
    );
  }

  Color _getPortTypeColor(PortType type) {
    // Return appropriate color based on port type
    switch (type) {
      // Map port types to appropriate colors
      default: return Colors.grey;
    }
  }

  @override
  bool shouldRepaint(JackPainter oldDelegate) {
    return oldDelegate.port != port ||
           oldDelegate.isHovered != isHovered ||
           oldDelegate.isSelected != isSelected ||
           oldDelegate.theme != theme;
  }
}
```

Enhance the JackConnectionWidget to display text labels and handle user interactions. This includes implementing tap, hover, and drag gesture detection with appropriate callbacks.

Implementation steps:
1. Update JackPainter to render text labels with proper positioning
2. Wrap the CustomPaint widget with GestureDetector for tap handling
3. Add MouseRegion for hover detection with animations
4. Implement drag gesture detection for connection creation

Example code:
```dart
@override
Widget build(BuildContext context) {
  return MouseRegion(
    onEnter: (_) => setState(() => isHovered = true),
    onExit: (_) => setState(() => isHovered = false),
    child: GestureDetector(
      onTap: () {
        setState(() => isSelected = !isSelected);
        widget.onTap?.call(widget.port);
      },
      child: GestureDetector(
        onPanStart: (details) {
          // Start drag operation
          widget.onDragStart?.call(widget.port, details.globalPosition);
        },
        onPanUpdate: (details) {
          // Update drag position
          widget.onDragUpdate?.call(details.globalPosition);
        },
        onPanEnd: (details) {
          // End drag operation
          widget.onDragEnd?.call();
        },
        child: Container(
          width: 80,
          height: 40,
          child: Row(
            children: [
              // Jack socket
              CustomPaint(
                size: Size(40, 40),
                painter: JackPainter(
                  port: widget.port,
                  isHovered: isHovered,
                  isSelected: isSelected,
                  theme: Theme.of(context),
                ),
              ),
              // Text label
              Expanded(
                child: Text(
                  widget.port.name,
                  style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.bodyMedium,
                  overflow: TextOverflow.ellipsis,
